4235,Levy's Of Hollywood,"

This family-owned, kosher eatery serves up traditional shawarma & kebabs in a low-key atmosphere.

column2: • For over 20 years, Levys kosher of hollywood has been synonymous with Middle Eastern fine dining.
• Liz Levy executive chef/owner takes the cuisine and culture of her homeland to the next level with a breathtaking restaurant and delicious cuisine.
• The Chef's mastery of traditional spices and flavors makes each dish an opportunity to experience classics and delicacies in new and exciting ways.
• Every plate becomes a culinary journey. Levys kosher of Hollywood also features homemade desserts to sophisticated tastes.
• For more information click here.

4048,Sun Harbour Boutique Hotel in Surfside,"

Surfside hotel with outdoor pool.

column2: • Set in a Italian-style building, this polished, all-suite hotel is a 2-minute walk from the nearest beach and 3 minutes from Bal Harbour Shops.

• Sophisticated 1- and 2-bedroom suites are accessed via exterior corridors and come with full kitchens, free WiFi and flat-screen TVs, as well as DVD players and living rooms with sofabeds. All have courtyard views.
• Amenities include a central courtyard with a heated outdoor pool and a terrace. Parking is complimentary.

1046,Sarah's Tent Kosher Market,"

Huge Kosher grocery store with extensive selection of meats, wine & much more.

column2: • Ample parking space.
• Great tip for travellers: Sarah' Tent offers ready to go, packed airplane size meals for $8.99.
• They are on the other side of the soups, next to the deli section. You can have them double wrapped, ready to microwave at your destination.
• Great pizza and bourekas in house.
• There are other Kosher restaurants, a Kosher ice cream shop, and a beautiful marina to go for a stroll, all located in the waterways shop.
• This is your one-stop-shop for all your Kosher needs. Catering service, deli, bakery, meat, pizzeria, wine, and so much more.

1067,List of Closed Waterways Kosher Restaurants,"KWB's Highlights:

column2: • Acqua Trattoria (closed)
• China Bistro (closed)
• There a China Bistro location open in Hollywood
• B&B Bistro (closed)
• Fuego moved to a new and much better location, 10 minutes south (moved)
• Karne, a steak house in the same store where Fuego used to be (open)
• Levy's Shawarma. This is their second location in the city (open)
• Noma (Dairy) is now in Waterways (open)
• The Ice Cream shop seems to have closed, but it's unclear. We've heard reports that both the Ice Cream and the coffee shops are now being run by the landlord.
• Florida’s wide array of delectable cuisine speaks to the sophisticated palates of food-savvy residents and visitors alike.
• Rustiko, although quite new, has gained a reputation for its exquisite flavors, aromas and ambiance that makes for an unforgettable experience.
• With presentation, texture and taste in mind, not a sense is left out of the experience when dining at Rustiko.
• The elegant tiled floors, vines hanging along the walls, and wood grain finishes enhance the feeling as though you’ve hopped on a plane to Italy.
• For more information click here.

4327,Carlos & Gabby's - Miami,"

Mexican eats plus a few American dishes, in simple, colorful digs.

column2: • Carlos & Gabby’s Smokehouse & Grill proudly continues in the tradition of its namesake to provide the all around best in kosher Mexican dining.

• Located in beautiful Miami Beach, another Carlos & Gabby’s has taken over!  Being close to the Miami Airport and beaches, it has been attracting and satisfying many hungry customers since November of 2015.
• With its comfortable booths, Mexican- American cuisine, and large and reasonably priced menu, this place is a perfect fit for all.
• Owners Aaron and Rachel visited the Carlos & Gabby’s of New York and fell in love with the idea of a Mexican themed restaurant. They then headed home and bought into the successful franchise.
• Different than the other Carlos & Gabby’s, this is a sit-down restaurant with waiter service. They have a large enough menu, where everybody could find something that they like.
• Other locations: Carlos & Gabby's - Riverdale, Carlos & Gabby's - Queens, Carlos & Gabby's Long Island and Carlos & Gabby's - Coney Island.

Contemporary space with cool lighting offers kosher Chinese & southeast Asian food, sushi & steaks.

column2: • If you're keeping kosher in South Florida, you don't have to settle for a falafel joint the next time you're looking for a place to eat.

• L'Chaim Asian Cuisine & Steakhouse is certified by the Orthodox Rabbinic Board with chefs who hand-pick the freshest local meats and vegetables and use a selection of imported spices, seasonings, and authentic ingredients to ensure a great kosher dining experience.
• The menu is dine-in or takeaway and offers a wide spectrum of cuisine from sushi to steak designed to satisfy a variety of dietary concerns and dining preferences.
• For more information click here.
• This place is pemanently closed.

column1:
4359,Bagel Time Cafe,"

Easygoing sandwich shop selling hearty deli fare including some kosher selections.

column2: • Fully renovated in the Summer of 2014, Bagel Time Café is a modern dairy restaurant in Miami Beach under new ownership.
• Those who know the area will remember the original Bagel Time for their basic breakfast and lunch options. Bagel Time Café however is a whole new and upgraded establishment.

• It’s been taken over by restaurant pros, Jay and Sharon Beck, who have years of restaurant management and culinary skill under their belts. They’ve turned the place into a must-visit destination. Walking into the café, it feels more like South Beach, than Miami Beach.
• The bright green décor is clean, modern and inviting. Although with free delivery anywhere in Miami you won’t even need to leave the beach to get a taste!

• Chef Jay Beck has plenty of experience in the restaurant business. He was the executive chef at the gourmet supermarket, Pomegranate in Brooklyn, as well as the chef and owner of Country Café in upstate New York.
• Bagel Time Café focuses on getting the freshest ingredients for their vegetarian, dairy based menu.
• For more information click here.

4285,Grand Cafe Espresso Bar,"

Coffee & espresso drinks plus Israeli breakfast & lunch fare in a casual space with outdoor seating.

column2: • Conveniently located on Stirling Road, minutes from I-95, Grand Café Sandwich Espresso Bar, a European-style Hollywood cafe offers a delightful menu, with coffee and blended drinks, friendly service, both indoor and outdoor seating, and a ""warm"" South Florida culinary experience.
• Founded in January 2012, the café owners and life-long friends Shay Yaakov and Meir Zafri created menu items that were based on nostalgic childhood food memories and recipes.

• After restaurant stints in Israel, Los Angeles and Texas, Shay and Meir moved to Miami and was instantly drawn to their current location. But most importantly, the address was the same as Shay’s birthday, 29-05.

• Whether it was a stroke of luck or a sign, the Grand Café Sandwich and Espresso Bar is a foodie destination, with a discernable family-style atmosphere of regular, loyal customers and a consistently delicious menu.
• For more information click here.

4289,Foozo Artisan Pizza,"

Kosher wood fired artisan pizza restaurant in Miami.

column2: • Dairy. Cholov Yisroel. Pas Yisroel. Yoshon pizza only. Bishul Yisroel Tuna.
• Foozo is true to the Italian tradition with an urban American twist. They bring us delicious wood-fired artisanal pizza along with other cheesy creations.
• Known for always being fast and friendly, Foozo is a great place to pick up a tasty quick meal. The great thin crust pizza with an amazing combination of toppings has people coming back for more.
• Try their margarita pizza, a Foozo sandwich, or build your own salad at their salad bar. Everything is super fresh and all menu staples come with tons of topping options!

• Choose from pizzas, fresh tossed salads, our very own “foozolis”, open top sandwiches and pasta. Their goal is to make something special to satisfy your heart's content. They serve delicious gluten-free pasta as well to satisfy a wide range of customers.
• Thanks to their app and delivery service you didn't have to leave the beach to enjoy Foozo’s creations!
• Located at Ojus, 18 miles north of downtown Miami.
• Eat-in, takeaways, and delivery.
• Plenty of good reviews.
• For more information about the menu, click here.
• Extra information click here.

4242,Lenny's Pizza (Miami Beach),"

Premier kosher pizza and dairy destination.

column2: • Walking down Arthur Godfrey Road, it's hard not to notice the unmistakable scent and look of authentic New York style pizza.

• The aroma itself seems to draw people through the doors.  Owner Jason Reiz has known the restaurant business ever since he can remember and has made it his life's long ambition to bring Floridians the perfect New York slice.

• ""Our philosophy is, to bring good quality wholesome kosher food to the masses"" says Jason. Opening its doors back in May of 2013, Lenny's has established quite a sizable following. It was also featured in Miami New Times as one of Five Top Kosher Restaurants in Miami, and being the only dairy one among them, it is effectively the best for kosher pizza in the area.
• For more information click here.

1050,The Harbour Grill,"

Sunny destination near Bal Harbour shops.

column2: • Harbour Grill Gourmet is one of the premiere Kosher restaurants in South Florida.
• It is known for using the finest ingredients as well as the best quality Kosher meats with their signature dry aging process.

• The Harbour Grill is the first to serve house-made Glatt Kosher charcuterie and high-end gourmet dishes. These high-end meats are extremely rare on the Kosher food market and they decided to make it available for you to enjoy in the comfort of your own house.
• They have recently opened their sister restaurant, Harbour Bistro, just a couple doors down.
• If you are looking for creative gastronomical dishes and in-house made charcuterie, in a relaxed atmosphere, 9427 Harding Ave. is unquestionably an address to recommend.

4308,China Kikar Tel Aviv,"

Kosher Chinese & European fare, plus Shabbat meals, in a condo-complex eatery with ocean views.

column2: • For over two decades, China Kikar Tel Aviv, has been a mainstay for Miami Beach locals and visitors alike.
• They are the longest standing Chinese kosher restaurant in town, while serving a wide variety of American dishes as well.
• Chinese-born owner, Bonnie Poon, has been in the restaurant business his whole life and amazingly spent 15 years living in Israel owning a Chinese restaurant there.
• In fact, he named the Miami Beach establishment after Kikar Dizenkof in the Israeli city of Tel Aviv.

column2: • Did we miss anything? Let us know in the comments below!

• Café Emunah is the only kosher restaurant in Fort Lauderdale and is mere steps from the Beach! It prides itself on offering an experience for your senses and an oasis for your mind, body and soul - a physical journey into your spiritual self.
• Upon entering, you feel enveloped by the warm and serene environment. The decor is upscale but sparse and features glass tables and blue fabric on the couches.

• Materials used in the restaurant are consistent with the eco-conscious elements of mysticism: napkins from recycled paper and pale blonde wood chairs that are ergonomic and simple in design, yet comfortable.
• The restaurant is also a tea bar and lounge with comfortable couches and a small library of books about Jewish mysticism.
• Its geographically central location makes it an ideal meeting spot for people in Miami to meet up with friends from Boca and the surrounding areas in between, such as Hollywood and Delray.

• It also makes for a convenient meal on the way to and from the airport, as it is only a 15-minute drive from the Ft. Lauderdale Airport. Café Emunah is the perfect ending to a day on the beach or a yummy preface to a romantic evening stroll.
• For more information click here.

4312,Chai Wok,"

Kosher establishment turning out a wide selection of Chinese dishes & sushi in a casual atmosphere.

column2: • Located a few blocks off Biscayne Blvd. and in the heart of North Miami Beach, you will find Chai Wok; a casual, yet sophisticated restaurant specialising in Authentic Chinese and American fare.
• The owner Donny Gordon, is a home-grown Florida native, which allows him to have that comfortable and natural feeling with his customers.

• In fact, he doesn't even like to use that word  - ""customers"" but rather family, since he has known many of them his whole life. And many of those years, incidentally, have been in the food business  - 18 years to be exact.
• Donny owned a very popular pizza store but decided to devote his full time in elevating Chai Wok to the restaurant he can be proud of.

• When he opened the restaurant in November of 2010, he decided to follow three basic but very important principles: Good service, consistency of food and cleanliness.  And the fact that you can find him in the restaurant at all times, does not go unnoticed by his ""family"" of diners.
• For more information click here.

4253,Kosh Miami,"

Steakhouse favourites, Asian dishes, and signature tapas.

column2: • South Florida now boasts a fine meat restaurant with a French flare since Kosh opened its doors in February 2013 to the delight of vacationers and local residents.
• The restaurant is led by owner Jean-Marc Benitah who many may know from his days as the owner of Juliette in Paris. Wanting to create that magic again, he moved to Florida to open Kosh.
• The location is just 2 blocks away from the beautiful Surfside beach, and steps away from many apartments, condos and hotels, making it a great destination for that leisurely yet upscale dinner.
• It’s also only a short walking distance from the famous Bal Harbour Shul and Young Israel of Bal Harbour, which comes in handy if you want to organise a private event for one of the Shabbat meals.

• The decor of Kosh is elegant contemporary with elements of art nouveau style: modern hanging lighting fixtures live in perfect harmony with more traditional chandeliers, as do mirrors and stylish photographs on the walls.

• Dark purple and grey color scheme with velvet chairs, soft purple light, and flowers on the tables adds to the atmosphere of regal luxury. Alternatively, you can sit at one of their outdoor tables to dine in that evening breeze.
• For more information click here.

4280,Grill Time Restaurant,"

A wide-ranging menu & spacious, contemporary location, draw diners to this glatt kosher steakhouse.

column2: • Decorated in a gold cream color scheme, Grill Time is set in a modern atmosphere with a touch of French Italian ambiance.
• Grill Time has a strong local following, and also attracts many out-of-town visitors who take advantage of the warm weather and hot location.

• After years in the restaurant business and working with a number of different cuisines, owners Eran Yousafan and Neil Karni decided that it would be exciting to fuse a number of dishes together to make something special.

• The restaurant is distinctive because it is so much more than meets the eye. You walk in thinking Middle Eastern food but you find a variety of international dishes that will engage both your eyes and your appetite.
• The owners believe that in order to make a restaurant a success, you must strive to set yourself apart from the crowd and be unique.
• For more information click here.

4218,Subres Grill,"

A kosher place with a homey feeling.

column2: • Glatt Kosher - Pas Yisroel - under full supervision - with Mashgiach.
• To find true hotspots when traveling to South Florida, you have to eat where locals eat, and local folks know where to find the best Middle Eastern and Mediterranean cuisines.
• SubresGrill is a relatively new restaurant which opened in December 2012 and owned by a warm Israeli couple, Eli and Etty Weinberg.
• This small quaint place has become a favorite with locals and tourists alike, with five-star reviews from grateful customers on Yelp, and other websites to attest to it.
• The restaurant is located in the middle of a vibrant Jewish neighborhood in North Miami, a few blocks to the west from Biscayne Blvd.
• The decor is simple and contemporary, in black and white hues with an addition of some purple and stainless steel, and features bar seating in addition to tables.
• Diners who walk in once, keep returning for the delicious fresh food, great service, and friendly atmosphere.
• The owner Eli shares that the key to the restaurant’s success is their love for what they do, combined with exceptional quality ingredients, and his wife’s unique cooking talent.
• For more information click here.
• OK Supervision

2838,Glick's Kosher Market,"

Glicks provides strictly Kosher deli meats, shiva, appetising prepared foods, delicatessen and also provides catering in Delray Beach, FL.

column2: • Glicks Legacy of Fine Foods started with a simple family-run Kosher meat market in Brooklyn, New York.

• In the early 1900's Sam Glick and his siblings emigrated from Russia and opened the first Glick Bros. Kosher Market. When Sam passed on, his wife Rachel and her sons Harold, Herman, and son-in-law, Jules Goldberg, took control of the business.

• Because of their commitment to Superior Quality Meats, Glick Bros. grew to become the largest Kosher Meat chains in New York. By the mid-1900’s, there were more than twenty Glick Bros. stores in operation throughout New York.
• In 1995, Jules son Gary relocated to south Florida with his family. Within a year Gary and his wife, Linda, built and opened Glicks Kosher Market in Delray Beach.
• By implementing all that he had learned from working with his father for over twenty years, the store was an instant success.
• In less than four years, Gary moved Glicks to a new location twice the size, creating a Kosher paradise.
• Glicks foundation has always been based on Superior Quality Kosher Meats. Since opening in Florida Gary has taken Glicks to a whole new level.
• Famous for its outstanding meat department, Glicks sells thousands of fresh soups and prepared meals weekly. Glicks Deli Counter is second to none.

• In store barrel cured deli meats, smoked fish and appetisers; including a sensational variety of over forty delicious homemade salads, hand rolled blintzes, homemade knishes, kreplach, petcha and scrumptious Matzo Balls are all a part of what makes Glicks a daily destination.
• For more information click here.

2820,Boca Beach Club,"

This posh beachfront resort is 2 miles from the Boca Museum of Art.

column2: • Great option for quick get away.
• 5 Kosher restaurants near by, on the beach.

• Vacations are redefined at Boca Beach Club, A Waldorf Astoria Resort. This oceanfront haven is a luxuriously modern oasis, while being part of the Mediterranean-inspired Boca Raton Resort & Club, and guests may enjoy all amenities and activities at both resorts.

• Enjoy lavish and sun-filled guest rooms, the world's top-rated spa, 11 restaurants and lounges, seven swimming pools, two acclaimed golf courses and endless recreation. Welcome to a truly peaceful retreat.
• Bliss out at Boca Beach Club, set on a private peninsula in Boca Raton, FL.

• REST: Guest rooms feature floor-to-ceiling sliding windows and dramatic views of the ocean. Stay in a Poolside Lanai Room and be steps from sinking your toes into the private beach. A Sky Deck Room has the perfect space to read, sip wine and watch the water.

• INDULGE: Treat yourself to a massage at the Waldorf Astoria Spa – rated the #1 Spa in the World by Condé Nast Traveler's Readers' Choice. Ever try a Ritual Bath? Be our newest devotee once you're relaxing amid the mosaics, marble and palace architecture. Sweeten your day more with a personalised facial or citrus body wrap.

• DINE: At Boca Beach Club, part of the Boca Raton Resort & Club, meals are memorable whether by the pool, ocean or snug in your guest room. From grab-and-go pastries to the award-winning Morimoto Sushi Bar, our 11 restaurants and lounges will be a highlight of your stay.

• PLAY: Tee off at two championship golf courses, or visit the famed tennis center or 30 courts to perfect your serve. Kids and adults alike will adore the FlowRider® Wave Simulator or a session at the Surf School by Billabong.
• For more information click here.

Contemporary option for elevated dining with a kosher menu featuring steaks, pasta dishes & tapas.

column2: • If you are ever in Boca Raton, Florida and are in the mood for a top quality steakhouse, Butcher Block Grill should be on your list.
• It’s the perfect place to catch dinner with the family after spending the day at the beach which is only a fifteen-minute drive away.
• The cuisine can be characterised as a mix of Mediterranean flavours and the classic American steakhouse.

• The rustic, trendy interior at Butcher Block Grill combines rich, dark wood and warm inviting colors to create the ideal setting for romantic dinners, family meals, corporate functions, and special occasions alike.
• For more information click here.

2833,Grove Kosher Market (Kosher Marketplace),"

Kosher supermarket located in Palms Plaza at Boca Del Mar.

column2: • The Grove Kosher Market is Florida’s Premier Glatt Kosher Market providing superior quality meats, poultry, fish, sushi, a wide assortment of freshly made salads, groceries, bakery, wines and our cooked foods section with soups, meats, fish, chicken, vegetables, and more. All prepared by their in house catering division.

• Whether you are buying ingredients to make a home cooked meal, stocking up for the holidays or want the delicious traditional cooked food favourites we are known for, The Grove Kosher Market is well worth the trip!
• For more information click here.

4303,Ditmas Kitchen Boca,"

Newest kosher restaurant to serve in Boca Raton.

column2: • Top Chef Alumnus Alex Reznik’s latest creation, Ditmas Boca, has become the newest kosher hot spot in Boca Raton since it opened in December 2016.

• His wildly popular Ditmas in Los Angeles has been a favourite of locals ever since it opened in 2014. The Boca location shares some of the original Ditmas menu’s classic items while introducing some innovative concoctions.
• Ditmas gets its name from the avenue in Brooklyn on which Reznik grew up, and nostalgia drove him to name the original Ditmas in LA as a tribute to his upbringing.
• Ditmas Boca is designed with lots of detail and love as Alex and his brother custom designed and built practically every inch of it.

• The decor is upscale contemporary with beautiful red banquettes lining the inside dining area, striking high back comfortable chairs and a large communal table that seats up to twenty in a semi-private room.
• Copper piping, restored wood, white subway tile, and exposed brick can also be found inside. The outdoor dining patio is nothing short of spectacular.
• The outside incorporates torches, white tablecloths, candles and exquisite chairs with a Palm Tree backdrop.
• The food is a conglomeration of different styles from various cultures - making it contemporary American food , but done with their own flair, with a solid culinary foundation.
• Everything is as farm-to-table-fresh as possible, including locally grown produce, freshly caught Floridian fish and exclusively American meat.
• Ditmas classics such as the Tony Fries, Signature Short Rib dish and Kale Caesar salad are just some of the most popular menu items.
• For more information click here.

column2: • 2-star hotel.

• This Chabad teams up with Aroma Market Catering to bring Kosher food to you! Their wide assortment of freshly-made salads, groceries, baked goods, and cooked meals are all prepared by their chefs in-house.
• They bake their own bread, cakes, and pastries on-site in their newly expanded bakery.
• Delivery is available so that it is convenient and affordable for you. For more information on how it works, click here.
<li>The hotel offers:
• 87 guestrooms.
• 3 restaurants.
• Outdoor pool.
• 24-hour front desk.
• Coffee/tea in a common area.
• Air conditioning.
• Daily housekeeping.
• Arcade/game room.
• Front desk safe.
• ATM/banking services.
• Laundry service.
• Conference space.
• Free continental breakfast, free wifi, and free parking.

8319,Chabad of Naples,"

Modern Chabad serving Jewish families in Naples.

column2: • Since 2003 the Alex & Carol Glassman Chabad Jewish Centre of Naples, has served Naples, Marco Island, and Greater Collier County.

• This Chabad teams up with Aroma Market Catering to bring Kosher food to you! Their wide assortment of freshly-made salads, groceries, baked goods, and cooked meals are all prepared by their chefs in-house.
• They bake their own breads, cakes, cookies and pastries on-site in their newly expanded bakery.
• By using the highest quality ingredients they bring to you the freshest and tastiest Kosher food available.
• Delivery is available so that it is convenient and affordable for you. For more information on how it works, click here.
• This Chabad offers programs designed to make Judaism an accessible reality to all Jews regardless of background or affiliation - or age!
• They provide a wide array of educational, humanitarian and social services for the growing Jewish community of Collier County.

• Chabad of Naples has just moved into its very own 22,000 square foot facility at the corner of Mandarin and Orchid just west of Tamiami Trail. You can click here to  view photos of the transformation.
• In 2011 they opened a Preschool of the Arts at the Chabad Jewish Community Centre. This preschool is available to children from 2 through 4 years old.
• By offering a stimulating yet friendly environment, children ages six through thirteen embrace their Jewish roots and gain a true sense of Jewish pride.
• If you would like to make a donation click here.
• More information about the Chabad of Naples Hebrew School, call 239-263-2620 or click here.
• Preschool information here!
• To join the women's circle, click here.

9036,"SummerPlace Inn Destin, Destin","

2-star hotel within walking distance of nearest Chabad.

column2: • 2 star hotel.
• 11 minutes walk from Chabad of Emerald Coast, Destin, Florida.
• Shabbat hospitality, enjoy an elegant Shabbat dinner on traditional Shabbat delicacies, with international Jewish flavours woven throughout the menu, complemented by a selection of kosher wines.
• Please make your reservation no later than one week in advance at chabad@chabademeraldcoast.org.

• Chabad is open to all, and do not charge their guests. However, it is encouraged to contribute towards their activities; your generous help will enable to keep a home open and assist many more visitors in the future.
• Each Shabbos meal costs us $25 for one adult and $15 for one child.
• This hotel is located 2.3 miles from Downtown Destin.

• 72 guestrooms, near the beach, Indoor pool and outdoor pool, fitness centre, business centre, 24-hour front desk, coffee/tea in a common area, air conditioning, daily housekeeping, front desk safe, ATM/banking services, laundry service, free wifi, and free parking
• For reservations click here.

13561,Chabad Russian Center,"

Friendly Chabad House with several activities suitable for families.

column2: • The Chabad Russian Center of S. Florida is founded and directed by Rabbi Alexander and Chanie Kalle.
• They are well known for creating the first Russian-Jewish early childhood programme in the area.
• Chabad Russian Center is proud to host a shul, which has a warm family atmosphere for people to daven / pray.
• They offer weekday minyan services, Shabbat and holiday services.
• Hebrew English Siddurim (prayer books) and Hebrew Russian Siddurim available.

• Celebrate a birthday, anniversary, or other special occasion, or commemorate the Yahrzheit of a loved one, by sponsoring a Kiddush.  $275 Co-Sponsor   |   $550  Kiddush (Standard)  |  $1000 Kiddush (Upgraded - contact them for details)
• For donations click here.
• Eruv information available here.
• You can also find them on Facebook.

13556,Chabad of Golden Beach,"

Warm and welcoming Chabad House.

column2: • This community is based on the three fundamental pillars of Judaism. Torah study, Tefila (prayer and connection with Hashem), and Gemilut Chasadim acts of love and kindness.
• For donations click here.
• Friday Night Services: Mincha followed by Kabbalat Shabbat 6:00 pm. Regular Mincha 6:15 pm

• Shabbat Children’s Program: 10:15 am. Main Minyan. Shacharit: 8:30 am, Rabbi’s Speech: 11:30 am. Kiddush: 12:00 pm, Torah Class: With Rabbi Chay Amar n/a. Mincha: 6:00pm Followed by Seuda Shelishit.
• Chabad Minyan: Shacharit: 9:45 am, Farbrengen: 12:15 pm, Mincha: 10 minutes before candle lighting Time.
• Shacharit: 7:30AM, Mincha & Arvit: 7:35 PM. Breakfast & Torah: 8:00 am.
• Wednesday Lectures: 9:00 pm with Rabbi Chay Amar and other Guest Speakers (for men and women).
• Hebrew School: Mondays & Wednesdays 4:00 pm (for school aged children – during the school year).

15916,Backyard BBQ,"

Smoked ribs & brisket, plus steak & seafood, served in a plank-walled storefront with a bar.

column2: • Walk into Backyard BBQ & Brew and be transported. The long, dark wood bar, wood paneled walls and handcrafted wooden chairs will take you from the middle of Miami to the wild, wild West.
• Just a few blocks away from the beach, this Surfside restaurant is the perfect place to go after a long day of fun in the sun.
• Backyard BBQ and Brew, true to its name, also has an impressive selection of wine and beer, with ten beers on tap, featuring beers from Miami’s own Wynwood Brewing Company.
• Whether you live in Florida or are there on vacation, let Backyard BBQ & Brew take care of you.

column1:
13571,Lubavitch Aventura South,"

Friendly and welcoming Chabad House.

column2: • Lubavitch Aventura South, which serves the south part of Aventura, is a branch of Friends of Lubavitch of Florida and the local centre of the worldwide Chabad Lubavitch movement.
• Their mikvah is open daily for members 7:45 a.m. – 8:15 a.m and Friday 1:00 p.m. – 3:00 p.m.
<li>Shacharit:
• Sunday 9:00 a.m.
• Monday to Friday 8:15 a.m.
• Shabbat 10:00 a.m.
• Daily Mincha: 6:30 p.m.
<li>Friday night:
• Mincha 6:30 pm.
• Ma’ariv: Kabalat Shabbat 30 minutes after mincha.
<li>Shabbat:
• Chaisdus 9:00 a.m.
• Shacharis 10:00 a.m.
• Torah Reading 10:45 a.m.
• Kiddush 12:00 p.m.
• Mincha 7:10 p.m.
• Followed by Seuda Shelishit, Ma’ariv and Havdallah.
• Shabbat dinners are free of charge but we encourage you to donate so they can continue helping fellow jewish travellers. For donations click here.
• Contact them in advance for Shabbat meals here.

2-star hotel within walking distance of nearest Chabad.

column2: • 2 star hotel.

• All meals are prepared under the supervision of the Orthodox Kashrut Committee of Tampa.
• If you have any queries then please don't hesitate to email to info@chabadofcentralflorida.com.
• This hotel is located 4.4 miles from Tampa Airport.
• 24 smoke-free guestrooms, air conditioning, daily housekeeping, computer station, self-serve laundry, limited hour front desk, free wifi, and free parking.
• For reservations click here.

9168,Chabad of Central Florida,"

Friendly Chabad in Tampa Florida.

column2: • Conveniently located, 3-minute walk to the Hyde Park Hotel, amazing synagogue, perfect for Shabbos in Tampa.
• Shabbat/Yom Tov Guest Rooms: There are rooms upstairs of the Shul available under reservation for Shabbat and holidays.
<li>Hotels nearby Chabad:
• 1. Hyde Park Hotel - (813) 254 2000 2105 W Bristol Avenue, Tampa, Florida This hotel is just one block away from Bais David!
• 2. Epicurean Hotel - (813) 999 8700 -1207 S Howard Ave (5-star hotel).
• 3. University Inn - (813) 253 0851 x0 830 W Kennedy Blvd.

• Chabad provides strictly kosher meals directly to your accommodation. They also provide packed lunches for day trips and picnics. All meals are prepared under the supervision of the Orthodox Kashrut Committee of Tampa.  If you have any queries then please don't hesitate to email to info@chabadofcentralflorida.com.

• The weekly Kiddush luncheon is sponsored by families in the community in a rotating fashion and because of their generosity, everyone that attends Chabad enjoys a delicious lunch. They would like to open the opportunity for sponsorship to you.
<li>MIKVAH ISRAEL OF TAMPA BAY Nightly By Appointment $18 YI Neshei* Member  $36 Non-Member.

column1: * Click here to find out more about YI Neshei Membership ($100 for the year) Shabbos and Yom Tov appointments are available.

9029,"Days Inn by Wyndham Destin, Destin","

2.5-star hotel within walking distance of nearest Chabad.

column2: • 2.5 star hotel.
• 10 minutes walk from Chabad of Emerald Coast, Destin, Florida.
• Shabbat hospitality, enjoy an elegant Shabbat dinner on traditional Shabbat delicacies, with international Jewish flavours woven throughout the menu, complemented by a selection of kosher wines.
• Please make your reservation no later than one week in advance at chabad@chabademeraldcoast.org.

• Chabad is open to all, and do not charge their guests. However, it is encouraged to contribute towards their activities; your generous help will enable to keep a home open and assist many more visitors in the future.
• Each Shabbos meal costs us $25 for one adult and $15 for one child.
• This hotel is located 1.7 miles from Downtown Destin.

• 60 guestrooms, near the beach, outdoor pool, 24-hour front desk, coffee/tea in a common area, air conditioning, daily housekeeping, self-serve laundry, free newspapers in the lobby, free wifi, and free parking.
• For reservations click here.
• Their burgers and steaks are certified Glatt-Kosher under the ORB and one-of-a-kind home-made.
• Great American Food
• Order Online

column1:
7673,"Chabad of Emerald Coast, Destin, Florida","

Modern and friendly Chabad House.

column2: • A home for all in Destin, Florida.

• Shabbat hospitality, enjoy an elegant Shabbat dinner on traditional Shabbat delicacies, with international Jewish flavours woven throughout the menu, complemented by a selection of kosher wines. Please make your reservation no later than one week in advance at chabad@chabademeraldcoast.org.

• Optional donation, Chabad is open to all, and do not charge their guests. However, it is encouraged to contribute towards their activities; your generous help will enable to keep a home open and assist many more visitors in the future. Each Shabbos meal costs us $25 for one adult and $15 for one child.
<li>There are many hotels, motels, and condos close to Chabad and the Synagogue. Some of them are:
• SummerPlace Inn.
• Club Destin Resort+.
• Pelican Beach ResortsDays InnHampton Inn and Suites.
• There is no Mikveh at the premises, please donate here.
• Synagogue Services: Every Friday eve at candle lighting time. Shabbat morning services at 10:00 am. Shabbat morning services are followed by full sit down Kiddush with delicious Cholent.
• For information on Kosher food in Destin, Florida, click here.

13422,Downtown Jewish Center Chabad- Fort Lauderdale,"

Regional headquarters of Chabad House, serving the Fort Lauderdale community since 2000.

column2: • DJCC - Bet Ovadia is the regional headquarters of Chabad, serving the Fort Lauderdale community since 2000.
• At DJCC everyone is welcomed like family. Children, adults, singles, couples, young and old feel at home. It is a great place to meet new friends.
• Friday evening Shabbat services at DJCC Spring Summer 5778. 7:00pm Mincha, 7:30pm Kabbalat Shabbat Day, Kabbalah & Coffee – 9:30am.
• Morning Service: 10:00AM, Kids Shabbat Programme ��� 11:30AM. Kiddush (light buffet lunch) follows the morning service.
• To sponsor a kiddush please contact our office (954) 667-8000 or email info@downtownjewish.com, to reserve for kabbalah and coffee email info@downtownjewish.com subject kabbalah and coffee.
• Morning Minyan: Mondays & Thursdays 8:00 AM at DJCC 900 E Broward Blvd, followed by a light breakfast and a Torah class.
• Visitor's information.

3755,Zayde's Kosher Kitchen,"

Central Florida's first full-Kosher premier catering service featuring international and American Kosher cuisine.

column2: • No special travel services.
• Located at one of Orlando’s award-winning meeting, convention, and vacation properties, Rosen Plaza Hotel, Zayde’s Kosher Catering is dedicated to delivering the highest quality Kosher catering.

• Offering on-site catering at all seven Rosen Hotels & Resorts, as well as off-site catering options; their talented culinary team led by Rosen Plaza’s Executive Chef Michael McMullen and Rosen Shingle Creek’s Executive Chef Jorge Oliveira, are committed to providing high-end, internationally-inspired Kosher cuisine, all within strict kashrut guidelines.
• Zayde’s state-of-the art Kosher culinary centre includes separate kitchens for Glatt Kosher meat, dairy, and pareve, all supervised by a full time on-site mashgiach.

9591,Riverside Mill Food Court – Port Orleans Riverside,"

INTERNAL NOTE: TMI. NO NEED FOR A STAND ALONE LISTING FOR ALL DISNEY RESTAURANTS.

column2: <li>Disney's Kosher Meals Information:
• Kosher meals can be accommodated at all table-service and select quick-service restaurants.
• Kosher meals should be requested 24 hours in advance by calling (407) WDW-DINE or (407) 939-3463.
• Guests under 18 years of age must have parent or guardian permission to call.

• For questions related to Kosher meals or other special dietary needs and requests, contact Disney at Special.Diets@DisneyWorld.com. Their Special Diets team is happy to assist you with any questions you have. (Source)
• Although, Kosher meals, either to dine in or ready to go, are available without advance request at Riverside Mill Food Court.
• However, we strongly suggest you call and follow procedures on our first bullet point.

• Kosher meals at Disney restaurants are provided by Weberman’s. Pricing varies by what you order, but quick service meals are priced between $9.99-11.99.  Table service meals vary by location and what you choose.
• At Weberman’s Traditional Foods, all of year-round & Passover products are prepared under the supervision of OU kosher certification.

3725,Whole Foods Orlando,"

Eco-minded chain with natural & organic grocery items, housewares & other products (most sell wine).

column2: • Whole Foods Market Orlando is more than just a grocery store, it's an experience!
• Located on the corner of Sand Lake Road and Turkey Lake Road, just west of Interstate 4.  It is minutes from all of your favourite Orlando attractions, a half mile from Chabad centre.
• This store features everything from fresh produce, meat and seafood, to a large grocery section of staple items including an expansive bulk grains and nuts section.
• They also have a variety of prepared foods and bakery products for your convenience, as well as full service coffee, juice and wine bar.
• Speaking of wine, they offer a large selection of wine and beer which pair perfectly with the amazing cheeses they feature from all over the world.

3688,ABC Commissary,"

Counter-service spot in Disney's Hollywood Studios offers global fast food amidst art deco decor.

column2: • Each of Disney parks contains one non-Kosher restaurant that serves airplane-style Kosher meals.
• This one serves typically hamburgers, hotdogs, macaroni & cheese.
• Overpriced and not very tasty.
• We recommend skipping this option and bring your own sandwiches instead.
<li>Each of Walt Disney World Florida's four parks contains one restaurant that offers Kosher meals without advance notice:
• In Animal Kingdom: Pizzafari (located on Discovery Island).
• In Epcot: Liberty Inn (located in the American Adventure Pavilion of the World Showcase).
• In Hollywood Studios: ABC Commissary (located in the Backlot).
• In Magic Kingdom: Cosmic Ray’s Starlight Café (located in Tomorrowland).
• When you enter one of the above four restaurants, you can ask for a Kosher menu at the counter. Meal choices tend to be hamburgers, hotdogs, macaroni and cheese and the like.
• In addition to the main dish, the meals tend to include a vegetable side dish, starch side dish, roll and dessert. Disney Kosher meals, all Glatt Kosher, come sealed in plastic packaging.
• Since the restaurant workers need to heat each meal individually in a microwave, it can be a bit of wait to get the meals after you order them at the counter.
• So it is a good idea to send one member of the family ahead by 10-15 minutes to order Kosher meals for the whole family.

3682,Quick Guide to Eating Kosher in Disney World Parks,"

General information on Kosher food at the Disney Parks and tips to enjoying experience more.

column2: • Disney allows you to bring food, drinks snacks without any hassle.
• The only rule is no loose ice.
• Some Disney restaurants offer ready to go (without reservation meals), while others require advanced reservation.
• Overpriced and not tasty, airplane style meals.
• We recommend skipping this option and bring your own sandwiches instead. But some travelers might like the convenience.

column1: Kosher Dining at Walt Disney World Parks

column2: • You can pre-order kosher meals at most Walt Disney World table service restaurants that accept reservations.
• Typically kid style menu include: Hamburgers, hotdogs, macaroni & cheese.
• Other options for adults, such as Matze Ball soup, garden salad, baked salmon, brisket and beef.
• When we called the cost seems to be $62 per adult and $37 per child.
• Under the OU Hashgacha.
• The key is to call (407) WDW-DINE or (407) 939-3463 at least 24 hours in advance.
• A prepayment is required to guarantee dining reservations.
• For a memorable and uniquely Disney experience, Kosher Character Dining and Dinner Shows can be arranged.

• Character Dining means that Disney characters, such as Cinderella or Winnie the Pooh, make rounds in the restaurant in which you are eating, stop at your table to say hello, and take photos together with you.

column1: List of Disney Park Restaurants that usually stock (no need to pre-order) ready to go kosher meals:

column2: • Animal Kingdom: Satu'li Canteen (in the new Pandora Land)
• Hollywood Studios: ABC Commissary
• Epcot Center: Liberty Inn - American Adventure, and at the Electric Umbrella
• Magic Kingdom: Cosmic Ray's Starlight Café - Tomorrowland
• All Star Food Courts: World Premiere (Movies) Intermission (Music) and End Zone (Sports)

column1: Caribbean Beach - Old Port Royale Food Court

column2: • Pop Century - Everything Pop Dining
• Port Orleans French Quarter - Sassagoula Floatworks and Food Factory
• Port Orleans Riverside - Riverside Mill Food Court
• Animal Kingdom Lodge: Phemora
• Disney's Grand Floridian - Gasparilla
• Saratoga Springs Resort - Artist's Pallete

column1: Kosher Dining at Walt Disney World Hotels

column2: • Disney Resorts table service restaurants that accept reservations can serve you by calling at least 24 hours ahead.

column1: Thank you Chabad Orlando for providing valuable information. Visit their site for even more: Chabad Orlando.
MUST READ: Tips for enjoying your visit to the park more.

column2: • Once inside the parks, walk left: For some reason, crowds tend to work towards the right. Walking to the left will probably mean less wait time.
• Disney tickets: Kids under 3 don't pay to enter the parks.
• Kid ticket price is from 3-9 years old.
• Annual passes cost the same for adults and kids.
• Parking costs $25 per day (Magic Kingdom).
• Most hotels offer free shuttle service or you can take an uber.
• Taking a train to any Disney resort will get you out of the park faster.
• Do you have more tips? Share them below and we will add them to the list for other Kosher Travelers to benefit.

3735,Catering By Motti,"

Open to the public  during Yeshiva Week only. Catering during the rest of the year.

column2: • A friendly and talented Kosher caterer that offers many traveler services.
• Yeshiva Week: Check their site for specials.
• Passover: They offer catering which combined with affordable homes in the area can make a great passover program alternative.
• During the rest of the year they provide catering for events, and food for Shabbat (including ability to order online).
<li id=""WPhtxlink"" class=""wp1link"">

column1: Catering By Motti is a Kosher catering company located in Orlando and serving the catering needs of clientele from Orlando area.

column2: <li class=""wp1link"">

column1: Established in 2000 at Natick, MA, with the goal to provide their clients with local fresh, high quality food that is visually appealing and delectable.

column2: <li class=""wp1link"">

column1: Their Kosher certified chefs offer all types of menu choices, ranging from the traditional to the unique, all done with an emphasis on quality, taste and with a flair for beautiful presentation.

column2: • Their professional staff will assist you in planning your Kosher event that exceeds your expectations: An elegant wedding reception, a Bat / Bar Mitzvah celebration, a Kiddush Luncheon, an informal backyard BBQ party, a falafel party, a corporate breakfast meeting or a Shabbat dinners at your home.
• Everything is possible and every detail will be handled with the highest level of Kashrut, care and attention to detail.

• Catering By Motti offers full service Glatt Kosher catering. It is Orlando’s premier off-premise Glatt Kosher catering whose venues include the finest hotels, synagogues, country clubs, yachts, as well as your home or office.

INTERNAL NOTE: AS DRAFT. NO REAL USE  SINCE THERE ARE SO MANY OPTIONS ONLINE.
Upscale Davenport vacation home with private pool and kitchen.

column2: • Great value, 4/5 rooms for $200 a day, including a private swimming pool.
• They charge an extra $25 a day for pool heating, useful in the winter.
• They have a small lazy river and fun public pool for a day off when not visiting parks.
• Has air Hockey and pool table in the garage.
• about 25 minutes south of Disney and Kosher restaurants.
• In our experience, it was nice and clean, but not nearly as nice as the pictures shown on hotels.com. This might depend on which house you get.
•  Seems safe for a stay during a hurricane.
• This hotel has 20 rooms.
• Credit card or cash deposit required.
• Government-issued photo ID required.
• Minimum check-in age is 18.
• Free WiFi in rooms and public areas.
• No pets allowed.
• Free self-parking.
• Smoke-free property.

9574,Kosher Quick Service Dining in Walt Disney World,"

Kosher meals to go at Disney parks and hotels!

column2: • Can't plan ahead? Kosher meals, either to dine in or ready to go, are available without advance request in the following restaurants at their respective parks.
• Cosmic Ray’s at Magic Kingdom Park in Tomorrow-land 10:00 AM – 10:00 PM.
• Liberty Inn at Epcot in World Showcase 11:30 AM – 8:30 PM.
• Electric Umbrella at Epcot in Future World 11:00 AM – 9:00 PM.
• ABC Commissary at Hollywood Studios in Commissary Lane 11:00 AM – 8:30 PM.
• Satu’li Canteen at Animal Kingdom in Pandora 11:00 AM – 9:30 PM.
• Kusafiri Coffee Shop and Bakery at Animal Kingdom in Africa 9:00 AM – 10:00 PM.
• World Premiere at All-Star Movies Resort 6:30 AM – 12:00 AM.
• Intermission at All-Star Music Resort 6:30 AM – 11:00 PM.
• End Zone at All-Star Sports Resort 6:30 AM – 11:00 PM.
• Old Port Royale Food Court at Caribbean Beach 6:30 AM – 12:00 AM.
• Everything Pop Dining at Pop Century 6:30 AM – 12:00 AM.
• Sassagoula Floatworks and Food Factory at Port Orleans French Quarter.
• Riverside Mill Food Court at Port Orleans Riverside 6:00 AM – 12:00 AM.
• Artist’s Palette at Saratoga Springs Resort 7:00 AM – 11:00 PM.
• Gasparilla Grill at Grand Floridian 24 hours.
• The Mara at Animal Kingdom Lodge 6:00 AM – 1:30 AM.
• For information on preorders of Kosher meals click here.

• Kosher meals at Disney restaurants are provided by Weberman’s. Pricing varies by what you order, but quick service meals are priced between $9.99-11.99 circa.  Table service meals vary by location and what you choose.
• At Webermans Traditional Foods, all of year-round & Passover products are prepared under the supervision of OU kosher certification.

9576,Walt Disney's Parks and Resorts Kosher Preorders,"

INTERNAL NOTE: WE MOVED THIS LISTING TO JUST ONE MORE INCLUSIVE ONE
Kosher meals available in any restaurant at Disney.

column2: • The preorder service works for people who get a holiday package with food included. When you book you can choose the restaurant, and then have the option to request Kosher or other dietary requirements.
•  You need to have a previous reservation, if you call 24 hours before to verify and confirm your option.
• You have up to 180 days before your stay to request Kosher meals and make restaurant reservations.
• Most Walt Disney parks and resorts table service restaurants that accept reservations can accommodate Kosher meals if requested at least 48 hours in advance.
• For pricing, ordering and any other questions about the Kosher meals offered, please call Walt Disney World Dining at 407-WDW-DINE.
• Kosher meals are available at the following Theme Park Food & Beverage locations with no advance notice needed:
• Disney's Animal Kingdom Theme Park: Satu'li Canteen and Tusker House Restaurant.
• Disney's Hollywood Studios: ABC Commissary.
•  Epcot: Liberty Inn and Electric Umbrella.
• Magic Kingdom Park: Cosmic Ray's Starlight Cafe.
• Please note that Kosher meals will also be readily available at Walt Disney World Resort Hotel Table-Service and Quick-Service/Food Court locations.
• For further information about their quick service dining click here.
• There is a link to some products available at their food and beverage locations that may satisfy your needs. Kosher Products:  http://wdw.wdpromedia.com/media/kana/sd/WDW-Kosher.pdf.

• Keep in mind that this is not the full list of all the options available, but represents many of their special dietary products. This means that some items considered ""regular menu offerings"" are not listed on the reference guides, despite still being appropriate for guests with special dietary needs.
• If a location is not listed, this does not mean they are not able to accommodate your request; however, some of the products that are found at other locations may not be available.

• If you have any last minute requests, we encourage you to speak with a Chef or Manager when you arrive at any dining location, and they will be happy to provide you with the most recent information available.
• Kosher menus vary from restaurant to restaurant and are subject to availability. Due to the special care taken to accommodate this dietary request, these meals may take longer to prepare.
• Kosher meals at Disney restaurants are provided by Weberman’s. At Weberman’s Traditional Foods, all of year-round & Passover products are prepared under the supervision of OU kosher certification.

INTERNAL NOTE: TMI. NO NEED FOR A STAND ALONE LISTING FOR ALL DISNEY RESTAURANTS.

column2: <li>Disney's Kosher Meals Information:
• Kosher meals can be accommodated at all table-service and select quick-service restaurants.
• Kosher meals should be requested 24 hours in advance by calling (407) WDW-DINE or (407) 939-3463.
• Guests under 18 years of age must have parent or guardian permission to call.

• For questions related to Kosher meals or other special dietary needs and requests, contact Disney at Special.Diets@DisneyWorld.com. Their Special Diets team is happy to assist you with any questions you have. (Source)
• Although, Kosher meals, either to dine in or ready to go, are available without advance request at The Artist's Palette.
• However, we strongly suggest you call and follow procedures on our first bullet point.

• Kosher meals at Disney restaurants are provided by Weberman’s. Pricing varies by what you order, but quick service meals are priced between $9.99-11.99.  Table service meals vary by location and what you choose.
• At Weberman’s Traditional Foods, all of year-round & Passover products are prepared under the supervision of OU kosher certification.

4-star hotel with 2 restaurants, near Universal Studios Florida™.

column2: • Within the Universal Orlando Resort complex, this chic, tropical island-themed hotel is 3 miles from the Orlando Eye observation wheel and 12 miles from Walt Disney World.

• Modern rooms come with flat-screen TVs, minifridges and free Wi-Fi. Upgraded rooms have lagoon or pool views, while suites add separate bedrooms, plus individual features such as balconies, wet bars, kids' bedrooms and/or kitchenettes.
• There are 4 themed restaurants and bars, plus a pool with waterfalls and slides. There's also a playground and a gym.
• Perks include free park shuttles, plus access to character events and early admission to The Wizarding World of Harry Potter.
• For more information click here.
• This restaurant is no longer kosher.

column2: • Shabbat dinner meals by reservation, usually served in the synagogue

10190,Fly to Key West for Lunch (ad),"

Fly you to Key West for lunch in a private airplane.
Are you in Miami but don't like the restaurants there? We feel your pain.
That's why we will take you, and up to two friends, to Key West for lunch, and get you back in Miami in time for dinner.

column2: • Get there in style. Arrive in your own private single engine airplane.
• Flight time is about 1.5 hours.
• Fly with experienced pilots.
• Cost: $900-$1300 total for up to 2 people, inclusive of fuel, pilot, landing fees.
• Your plane will be a Cirrus SR22 or similar. The only plane of it's kind that features a parachute.
• KWB will arrange for the passenger seating in the front to have a try at the controls for a few minutes.
• Impress your shidduch date, celebrate your anniversary, or have a great time with friends.
• Have lunch at Mam's Kosher Restaurant in Key West, explore the city and come back the same night.
• Would you like to stay a few nights? We will arrange for the pilot to pick you up again for $800.
• Heading to Tampa, Orlando, Tallahassee, or any other city in Florida, just let us know.
• Subject to availability, weather, and other factors.
